"{\"uid\": \"abc.net.au-listen-programs-news-specials-trans-swimmer-barred-from-competing-in-paris-olympics-103975756\", \"text\": \"Program:News Specials  The American transgender swimmer Lia Thomas has lost a court case against swimming government body World Aquatics.  It means Thomas will not be competing in the Paris Games.  Back in January, Thomas took World Aquatics to the Court of Arbitration for Sport over its new rules which ban anyone who has undergone \\\"any part of male puberty\\\" from competing in the female category.  ABC NewsRadio's Sarah Dingle spoke with Dr Catherine Ordway - the Sport Integrity Research Lead at the University of Canberra.  The American transgender swimmer Lia Thomas has lost a court case against swimming government body World Aquatics, which means she will not be competing in the Paris Olympic Games.(ABC News: Kathleen Dyett)  Published:18 Jan 2025Sat 18 Jan 2025 at 12:00am  Published:7 Jan 2025Tue 7 Jan 2025 at 10:30pm  Published:6 Jan 2025Mon 6 Jan 2025 at 10:30pm  Published:6 Jan 2025Mon 6 Jan 2025 at 12:00am  Download the ABC listen app for free music podcasts and playlists  We acknowledge Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples as the     First Australians and Traditional Custodians of the lands where we     live, learn and work.\"}"